<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - REAR OIL SEAL REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REAR OIL SEAL REMOVAL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Flywheel Housing Installed</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is not necessary to remove the flywheel housing or oil seal carrier, if all that is being
                        replaced is the oil seal and wear sleeve.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Remove rear oil seal as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Punch two holes into the rear oil seal at the 3 and 9 o'clock positions. Insert two
                    sheet metal screws into these holes (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_169.xml" xrefid="ef1600707">7.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a slide hammer, alternately pry on each screw to remove rear oil seal from the
                    carrier (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_169.xml" xrefid="ef1600708">7.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ). Discard old oil seal.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
